******
[1] Pakistan - Balochistan, media report
Date: Thu 6 Jul 2017
Source: Dawn [edited]
https://www.dawn.com/news/1343576/chaman-infant-diagnosed-with-polio


A polio case has been detected in Chaman, a town along the Pak-Afghan border in Qila Abdullah district.

In 2016, 20 cases were reported from across the country out of which 2 were from Qila Abdullah.

The 18-month-old son of a resident of Mohalla Rah Mohammad in Mehmoodabad, was diagnosed with the poliovirus on [Mon 3 Jul 2017] in what is being termed by the health officials as the 1st case reported in Balochistan this year [2017].

On [Wed 5 Jul 2017], the health department claimed that the child's mother and grandmother had refused to get him vaccinated. They said the boy had hardly received 2 to 3 doses of the vaccine since he was born.

The child's father said that they got alarmed when [the boy] was running a high fever and was constipated. He was taken to a local dispensary and later to the children's hospital in the area, where doctors suspected the child was suffering from the crippling disease. Health officials said that after the child's stool samples were taken and other medical tests were carried out, it was confirmed that he was suffering from polio.

The next polio eradication campaign in the province is scheduled for [24 Jul 2017].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail (Alerted to case by HealthMap Alert)
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The media report suggests that the stool specimens were positive for poliovirus but does not mention the genetic typing whether the virus is a wild poliovirus (WPV) or a vaccine derived poliovirus (VDPV). [According to the EpiCore report below it is WPV1 - Mod.LM] The below weekly report from the Global Polio Eradication Initiative (GPEI) does not mention the above case, suggesting the genetic typing of the virus was most likely still pending at the time of the report. It should be noted that this case comes from a town by the Pakistan/Afghanistan border, a region that has been identified as high risk for poliovirus transmission, where there have been periodic positive environmental samples. Using the drafted version of this post, I sent an RFI out to the EpiCore Surveillance Project members and received responses with the information I had requested. See below.

The media report does mention the family withheld vaccination from the child that had possibly received less than 3 doses - a pity. This part of Pakistan is one of the areas with high resistance to vaccination and where there has been periodic violence directed towards vaccination workers. [The EpiCore report below supports that vaccine refusal was involved in this case. - Mod.LM]

A map showing the location of Chaman town near the Afghan border can be found at https://i1.wp.com/www.politicpk.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Killa-Abdullah-District-Map-with-Tehsils-Complete.gif?fit=688%2C600&ssl=1.

The HealthMap/ProMED map of Pakistan can be found at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5155739,140. - Mod.MPP]

