[2] Pakistan - Balochistan, EpiCore Surveillance Project
Date: 6 Jul 2017
Source: EpiCore Surveillance Project

[a]
The NIH Islamabad has confirmed the virus as a WPV1

Responding Member: Zulfiqar Ali
PEI- WHO Sindh

--
[b]
This is the 3rd case in Pakistan this year (2017) and the 1st case from the Quetta block. The child is from a refusal family. The mother hides the child as per the grandfather's pressure. It is from a district Killah Abdullah in the same UC [Union Council] which reported a last case in 2016.

Responding Member: Dr. Muhammad Hakim
FELTP Pakistan

--
Communicated by:
EpiCore Surveillance Project Members

[Our thanks goes out to the EpiCore Surveillance Project members Drs. Zulficar Ali and Muhammad Hakim for their rapid replies to our RFI for more information on the laboratory findings on this case. As this case had a WPV1 isolated, genetic testing on the isolate might assist in identifying where this virus was last identified. - Mod.MPP]

